name: Bakmi Bang Bara
address: Jl. Mahendradatta Utara No.55, Padangsambian, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80119, Indonesia
review 1:
One of the best noodles in town!!!
Must visit
The taste is ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐
The price is quite cheap
Super worth it!
Been here twice and will visit again and again!
Minus is only the place to eat is outdoor only so it's quite hot at afternoon and the parking lot is small 🙏
review 2:
Love it, the texture of the noodles its nice i like it, mie yamin good, bakmie ayam good, mix bakso and pangsit kuah was good, kwetiaw was good.

The broth only lil bit to tasteless, i think if they put more salt and lil bit of sesame oil will be more good.
Price its so affordable.
Portion of the noodles good.

They have a new proper place now, in front of the mart.

They have 2 times to served 10am-2pm and 4pm-6pm ( if still available)
And try to come early so the acar timun and acar cabe rawit hijau still there.

But overall for the price and taste good noodles bar in Denpasar, this gonna be my favorite so far.
review 3: not worth the wait. service was slow, with a lot of orders and queue, they need to be fast enough to serve those many orders. food just ok, too salty and too sweet for me personally. I like Mie Bandung more than this bakmi. price is cheap, that's the only good thing about this place.
review 5: Sellers too slow. Taste just okay

address: Pemecutan Kaja, Denpasar Utara, Denpasar City, Bali 80118, Indonesia
review 1: It’s a home that sell a some food, look small in front but quite wide inside. Homey place to having lunch. The Tempong Babi is so good with affordable price. They have pork mostly. The second floor space is nice .
review 2: The pork tempong was really great, anyone near here should try it the place is a bit hidden and you can park outside for motorcycle and cars. 👍👍👍
review 3: All good, samsam pork very delicious
review 4:
Perfect.. as pork lover you must try this one,
Tasty but not pricey

name: Ayam bakar ku gunung agung
address: Jl. Gn. Agung No.112, Pemecutan, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80111, Indonesia
review 1: We had the spicy and sweet grilled chicken. It was extremely quick service and was absolutely delish food. The staff were excellent and could not be faulted. I will return. Yummmmm.
review 2: The taste is not to be doubted, especially with several variants of spices that we can choose from such as spicy, or sweet spicy. For those who can't eat spicy, my advice is to inform the cashier that it's just a little spicy.
review 3: I just bought grilled chicken here..fast m good service.

review 1: Ok, as far as kosts go the size is good, but the balcony is cm away from the next building ... No view
review 2: The road was unpaved ...and bit dirty place..

name: Rumah Makan Padang SARASO Asli Masakan Padang
address: Jl. Buluh Indah No.14, Pemecutan Kaja, Kec. Denpasar Utara, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80118, Indonesia
review 1: Special restaurant for Padang cuisine.  A clean place with good food is perfect for you lovers of Padang food with spices and coconut milk.  In addition to the waitress, the owner is also very friendly and helpfull to the consumers.
review 2:
The worst nasi padang experience. Or maybe my expectations were too high.

We had 2 meals; one is rice with chicken, beef lungs, perkedel, the other is rice with beef lungs, beef skin. We also ordered iced tea and orange.

The food was totally not worth the price tag of IDR 125K. Not to mention the portion was barely filling. I've had much better nasi padang for cheaper.

Will never come back here even if it's the last palce to eat on earth.
review 3: Here, you can buy a portion only for food and choose what you like. Affordable price & delicious especially the Rendang
review 4: I came 21.38 during ramadhan,expecting to have a big meal after fasting. But only received half portion of rice, so are my wife and kids. When i asked for some more rice,he said it is out, habis. So i only had 1/2 portion. Then when we need to pay in the end, all meals were charged as full portion. Such a rip off warung padang. I know its pricy to eat there but i just didnt expect them to charge unequally. Surely will never come back,thanks for lessons..
review 5: Love the food, people are so nice, mashallah 🙏🙏🙏

review 1: The place small and cozy, the takoyaki delicious 🤤. we coming there for kids cooking class, the event was amazing my daughter enjoyed every moment. 👍🏾👍🏾
review 2:
Very happy we accidentally stumbled on this place. Great Gyoza. Great iced coffee, it was sweet strong and cold, best we’ve had in Bali so far!
Power points and wifi.

name: Sate Taichan NyotNyot
address: Jl. Mahendradatta Selatan No.6, Pemecutan Kaja, Kec. Denpasar Utara, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80111, Indonesia
review 1:
I went there because it’s close to my house. The Taichan costs 25,000 rupiahs for just the skewers without rice, and they were out of stock for almost everything. No grilled Taichan, no lontong, and they only had cola, Frestea, and cold water for drinks.

I ordered two portions of fried Taichan for 25,000 rupiahs, and the table was dirty, so I had to clean it with a tissue. It was really dirty. I thought about taking the food to go, but they were about to serve it, so I decided to eat there. After the food arrived, the staff just sat around, playing on their phones and lying down. Yes, they were lying down.

The Taichan sambal was good, but the chicken was just okay, a bit tough. I won’t go back there. I’m really sorry. ☹️
review 2: Food is amazing, sate is enak🔥

name: Wang Korean Street Food
address: Jl. Gn. Agung No.137, Pemecutan, Kec. Denpasar Utara, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80111, Indonesia
review 1:
The best Korean chicken in Bali 💯🫶🏻
The chicken is crispy on the outside yet juicy and tender on the inside🤤🤤.
I highly recommend trying their Soy Garlic and Gochujang Yangnyeom Chicken🏅.
Tteokbokki is also one of my favorites because it's chewy and authentic✨️.
review 2: Please this is a must-try Korean food in Denpasar! Their Garlic Chicken thingy is a bomb 🤤🤤🤤
review 3: My 2nd times here ! Affordable price, good taste, friendly service :)
review 4:
I often eat here, because the food tastes very good, the place is very easy to find, parking is also available, it's open until late so you don't need to worry.
the owner is very friendly and kind, the service is very good, the place is comfortable and also very clean.
all the menu taste good, i really like this place 😍🥰❤️

review 1: When quite, the place is so energizing. Perfect for study and working. This place’s open till 12 which is really convenient.
review 2: The coffee and pastry are amazing
review 3: food and service very good. highly recommended place

review 1: Small shop of satay plecing but a very nice owner, unlike arjuna (worst service and not polite ). A good sized meat skewers with nice sambal plecing. Not crowded too.
review 2: Love it! Highly recommended! Decent portion! Great attitdude from the owner!

name: Paon Siap
address: Jl. Gn. Agung No.121, Pemecutan, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80119, Indonesia
review 1: Authentic Balinese Nasi Campur with cheap price. This is Nasi campur ayam betutu lengkap with extra satay for only 20K. Open in the morning until finish, usually max by 1pm. Super crispy chicken skin and their satay is winner! One of my favorite of all Time! #supportlocalbusiness
review 2: One of the best Balinese dish I’ve ever tried. Best satay ever!!!
review 3: I loved all of their Balinese food, the taste of the food is very authentic. The prices are adorable. You can also order for catering and party. My favorite is Sate Pelecing and Ayam asap betutu the best. Oh ya the owner was sooo nice..
review 4: Thank God for paon siap.. delicious food, decent price, and the owner was very friendly since she's my old friend on campus.. lol.. good luck kez.. as promise, here's my review for your cozy place..
review 5: in my opinion, they serve the best sisit sapi, sisit ayam, and plecing satay in the world
